Found it. Limine line ~193 in `common/protos/limine.c`:

```c
// Map 0->4GiB range to HHDM if base revision < 3
if (base_revision < 3) {
    map_pages(pagemap, direct_map_offset, 0, VMM_FLAG_WRITE, 0x100000000);
}
```

I asked for base revision **3**, so the blanket "first 4 GiB → HHDM" mapping that includes device memory like PL011 is *deliberately not created*. Revision 3 only maps memmap entries with specific types. Dropping back to revision 2 gives us PL011 access via HHDM with no MMU code on our side. Let me revert the sentinel and lower the base revision.

